## Chapter 1 — Overview

### 1.1 Introduction

The project addresses the challenges of traffic congestion and inefficient lane management. Traditional road dividers are static and unable to adapt to changing traffic patterns, causing delays and accidents. By integrating the ESP8266 microcontroller, IoT technology, and image processing, this system enables dynamic lane adjustments based on real-time traffic data.

Cameras and sensors capture traffic conditions, which are analyzed to control the divider's movement automatically. The ESP8266 ensures cost-effective wireless connectivity and efficient data processing. This innovative solution enhances traffic flow, reduces accidents, and promotes smarter urban traffic management.

### 1.2 Motivation

Traditional fixed dividers often fail to adapt to dynamic traffic patterns, leading to congestion and delays. By leveraging IoT technology, this system enables real-time adjustments to lane distribution based on traffic flow, improving efficiency during peak hours or emergencies. The automated and remote-controlled mechanism ensures minimal human intervention, reducing errors and labor costs. Additionally, it supports better resource utilization, minimizes accidents caused by improper lane usage, and contributes to smarter, more sustainable urban infrastructure.

