## Chapter 4 — ESP8266 in Traffic Management

The ESP8266 microcontroller hosts a lightweight HTTP web server over a soft Access Point (AP). A mobile application sends HTTP GET requests with a `State` parameter to control motor direction and speed.

**Key capabilities:**
- Creates a Wi-Fi AP (`Make DIY`) — no router needed
- Handles 8 movement directions plus stop
- Supports 10-level PWM speed control (400–1023)
- Responds to commands with <10ms latency on local network

See the full annotated source code in `src/esp8266/esp8266_motor_control.ino`.

