## Chapter 6 — Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrated a proof-of-concept for an IoT-based movable road divider. By combining embedded systems (ESP8266), computer vision (YOLOv5 TFLite), and motor control (L298N), the system can dynamically respond to traffic conditions with minimal human intervention.

The custom NumPy-based NMS implementation proved lightweight and effective for Raspberry Pi deployment. The ESP8266 web server provided reliable, low-latency remote control over a local Wi-Fi AP.

### Future Scope

- Integrate image processing output directly with motor control (close the feedback loop)
- Replace Wi-Fi AP with 4G/LTE for city-scale deployment
- Develop a web dashboard with real-time traffic analytics
- Explore solar-powered operation for roadside installation
- Evaluate Coral Edge TPU for accelerated on-device inference

